{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FVKL5fFwfAKNmcSCuXFzTR","type":"tool_result","content":"# 2026 Federal Income Tax Brackets\n\nBased on the webpage content provided, the IRS released 2026 tax brackets for **single filers and married filing jointly only**. The document states:\n\n**Single Taxpayers:**\n- 10% for incomes of $12,400 or less\n- 12% for incomes over $12,400\n- 22% for incomes over $50,400\n- 24% for incomes over $105,700\n- 32% for incomes over $201,775\n- 35% for incomes over $256,225\n- 37% for incomes over $640,600\n\n**Married Filing Jointly:**\n- 10% for incomes of $24,800 or less\n- 12% for incomes over $24,800\n- 22% for incomes over $100,800\n- 24% for incomes over $211,400\n- 32% for incomes over $403,550\n- 35% for incomes over $512,450\n- 37% for incomes over $768,700\n\n**Important limitation:** The article does not include tax bracket information for head of household or other filing statuses. The source material notes \"Visit the IRS website for more tax tables and additional details,\" indicating this publication focused only on the two major filing categories."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9ec58da6-4ff1-4815-8056-168ff90521c1","uuid":"ff02f583-8c78-4211-9a2e-8995d0de74aa","tool_use_result":{"bytes":1409024,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# 2026 Federal Income Tax Brackets\n\nBased on the webpage content provided, the IRS released 2026 tax brackets for **single filers and married filing jointly only**. The document states:\n\n**Single Taxpayers:**\n- 10% for incomes of $12,400 or less\n- 12% for incomes over $12,400\n- 22% for incomes over $50,400\n- 24% for incomes over $105,700\n- 32% for incomes over $201,775\n- 35% for incomes over $256,225\n- 37% for incomes over $640,600\n\n**Married Filing Jointly:**\n- 10% for incomes of $24,800 or less\n- 12% for incomes over $24,800\n- 22% for incomes over $100,800\n- 24% for incomes over $211,400\n- 32% for incomes over $403,550\n- 35% for incomes over $512,450\n- 37% for incomes over $768,700\n\n**Important limitation:** The article does not include tax bracket information for head of household or other filing statuses. The source material notes \"Visit the IRS website for more tax tables and additional details,\" indicating this publication focused only on the two major filing categories.","durationMs":5495,"url":"https://copera.org/pera-on-the-issues/irs-releases-2026-tax-brackets-contribution-limits-other-tax-updates"}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01EoeHMUgu1J73y5vLuJVtxL","type":"tool_result","content":"# 2026 Federal Income Tax Brackets - Complete Filing Status Comparison\n\nBased on the webpage content, here are the complete 2026 IRS tax brackets for all filing statuses:\n\n## Tax Bracket Table\n\n| Tax Rate | Single | Married Filing Jointly | Head of Household | Married Filing Separately |\n|----------|--------|----------------------|-------------------|------------------------|\n| 10% | Up to $12,400 | Up to $24,800 | Up to $17,700 | Up to $12,400 |\n| 12% | $12,401–$50,400 | $24,801–$100,800 | $17,701–$67,450 | $12,401–$50,400 |\n| 22% | $50,401–$105,700 | $100,801–$211,400 | $67,451–$105,700 | $50,401–$105,700 |\n| 24% | $105,701–$201,775 | $211,401–$403,550 | $105,701–$201,750 | $105,701–$201,775 |\n| 32% | $201,776–$256,225 | $403,551–$512,450 | $201,751–$250,500 | $201,776–$256,225 |\n| 35% | $256,226–$640,600 | $512,451–$626,350 | $250,501–$626,350 | $256,226–$640,600 |\n| 37% | Over $640,600 | Over $768,700 | Over $626,350 | Over $640,600 |\n\n## Key Observations\n\nThe article notes that \"the IRS adjusts federal income tax brackets every year to account for inflation.\" Importantly, Head of Household thresholds for the 24% bracket ($105,701–$201,750) and 32% bracket ($201,751–$250,500) differ from Single filers, providing broader income ranges at lower marginal rates.\n\nThe content explains that these adjustments represent \"inflation-adjusted thresholds\" designed to prevent bracket creep while maintaining the seven-tier progressive tax structure."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9ec58da6-4ff1-4815-8056-168ff90521c1","uuid":"0f74a847-9d05-41d6-bdb3-c2f912a7cae2","tool_use_result":{"bytes":150458,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# 2026 Federal Income Tax Brackets - Complete Filing Status Comparison\n\nBased on the webpage content, here are the complete 2026 IRS tax brackets for all filing statuses:\n\n## Tax Bracket Table\n\n| Tax Rate | Single | Married Filing Jointly | Head of Household | Married Filing Separately |\n|----------|--------|----------------------|-------------------|------------------------|\n| 10% | Up to $12,400 | Up to $24,800 | Up to $17,700 | Up to $12,400 |\n| 12% | $12,401–$50,400 | $24,801–$100,800 | $17,701–$67,450 | $12,401–$50,400 |\n| 22% | $50,401–$105,700 | $100,801–$211,400 | $67,451–$105,700 | $50,401–$105,700 |\n| 24% | $105,701–$201,775 | $211,401–$403,550 | $105,701–$201,750 | $105,701–$201,775 |\n| 32% | $201,776–$256,225 | $403,551–$512,450 | $201,751–$250,500 | $201,776–$256,225 |\n| 35% | $256,226–$640,600 | $512,451–$626,350 | $250,501–$626,350 | $256,226–$640,600 |\n| 37% | Over $640,600 | Over $768,700 | Over $626,350 | Over $640,600 |\n\n## Key Observations\n\nThe article notes that \"the IRS adjusts federal income tax brackets every year to account for inflation.\" Importantly, Head of Household thresholds for the 24% bracket ($105,701–$201,750) and 32% bracket ($201,751–$250,500) differ from Single filers, providing broader income ranges at lower marginal rates.\n\nThe content explains that these adjustments represent \"inflation-adjusted thresholds\" designed to prevent bracket creep while maintaining the seven-tier progressive tax structure.","durationMs":7822,"url":"https://swatadvisors.com/irs-tax-brackets-for-2026/"}}
