{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0169vxJTX6v28pVYP32VmFHh","type":"tool_result","content":"# 2026 Federal Income Tax Brackets\n\nBased on the article, here are the complete 2026 tax brackets:\n\n## Head of Household\n- 10%: $0 - $17,700\n- 12%: $17,701 - $67,450\n- 22%: $67,451 - $105,700\n- 24%: $105,701 - $201,750\n- 32%: $201,751 - $256,200\n- 35%: $256,201 - $640,600\n- 37%: Over $640,600\n\n## Married Filing Separately\n- 10%: $0 - $12,400\n- 12%: $12,401 - $50,400\n- 22%: $50,401 - $105,700\n- 24%: $105,701 - $201,775\n- 32%: $201,776 - $256,225\n- 35%: $256,226 - $384,350\n- 37%: Over $384,350\n\n## Married Filing Jointly / Qualifying Surviving Spouse\n- 10%: $0 - $24,800\n- 12%: $24,801 - $100,800\n- 22%: $100,801 - $211,400\n- 24%: $211,401 - $403,550\n- 32%: $403,551 - $512,450\n- 35%: $512,451 - $768,700\n- 37%: Over $768,700\n\nThe document notes that \"tax-bracket thresholds increase for each filing status\" with higher brackets experiencing larger dollar increases due to inflation adjustments."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9ec58da6-4ff1-4815-8056-168ff90521c1","uuid":"12da3590-4f32-4304-8b3f-a68c0e4ae2fc","tool_use_result":{"bytes":425730,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# 2026 Federal Income Tax Brackets\n\nBased on the article, here are the complete 2026 tax brackets:\n\n## Head of Household\n- 10%: $0 - $17,700\n- 12%: $17,701 - $67,450\n- 22%: $67,451 - $105,700\n- 24%: $105,701 - $201,750\n- 32%: $201,751 - $256,200\n- 35%: $256,201 - $640,600\n- 37%: Over $640,600\n\n## Married Filing Separately\n- 10%: $0 - $12,400\n- 12%: $12,401 - $50,400\n- 22%: $50,401 - $105,700\n- 24%: $105,701 - $201,775\n- 32%: $201,776 - $256,225\n- 35%: $256,226 - $384,350\n- 37%: Over $384,350\n\n## Married Filing Jointly / Qualifying Surviving Spouse\n- 10%: $0 - $24,800\n- 12%: $24,801 - $100,800\n- 22%: $100,801 - $211,400\n- 24%: $211,401 - $403,550\n- 32%: $403,551 - $512,450\n- 35%: $512,451 - $768,700\n- 37%: Over $768,700\n\nThe document notes that \"tax-bracket thresholds increase for each filing status\" with higher brackets experiencing larger dollar increases due to inflation adjustments.","durationMs":5521,"url":"https://www.doeren.com/viewpoint/irs-releases-2026-cost-of-living-adjustments-includes-amendments-from-obbba"}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01S4g7asQE3ArNLSdFzA6Ymm","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"IRS 2026 \"head of household\" tax brackets \"$201,750\" OR \"$201,775\" revenue procedure 2025-32\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"IRS releases tax inflation adjustments for tax year 2026, including amendments from the One, Big, Beautiful Bill | Internal Revenue Service\",\"url\":\"https://www.irs.gov/newsroom/irs-releases-tax-inflation-adjustments-for-tax-year-2026-including-amendments-from-the-one-big-beautiful-bill\"},{\"title\":\"2026 Tax Brackets and Federal Income Tax Rates | Tax Foundation\",\"url\":\"https://taxfoundation.org/data/all/federal/2026-tax-brackets/\"},{\"title\":\"Federal income tax rates and brackets | Internal Revenue Service\",\"url\":\"https://www.irs.gov/filing/federal-income-tax-rates-and-brackets\"},{\"title\":\"26 CFR 601.602: Tax forms and instructions.\",\"url\":\"https://www.irs.gov/pub/irs-drop/rp-25-32.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"2026 Inflation Adjustments for Tax Professionals: Revenue Procedure 2025-32 Analysis — Current Federal Tax Developments\",\"url\":\"https://www.currentfederaltaxdevelopments.com/blog/2025/10/9/2026-inflation-adjustments-for-tax-professionals-revenue-procedure-2025-32-analysis\"},{\"title\":\"MOAA - IRS Releases Inflation-Adjusted 2026 Tax Brackets\",\"url\":\"https://www.moaa.org/content/publications-and-media/news-articles/2025-news-articles/finance/irs-releases-inflation-adjusted-2026-tax-brackets/\"},{\"title\":\"2026 IRS Tax Brackets, Standard Deductions, Capital Gains +AMT\",\"url\":\"https://millancpa.com/insights/2026-irs-tax-brackets-standard-deductions-capital-gains-amt\"},{\"title\":\"Federal Tax Filing Statuses | Congress.gov | Library of Congress\",\"url\":\"https://www.congress.gov/crs-product/IF13143\"},{\"title\":\"2025-2026 Tax Brackets & Federal Income Tax Rates | H&R Block®\",\"url\":\"https://www.hrblock.com/tax-center/irs/tax-brackets-and-rates/what-are-the-tax-brackets/\"},{\"title\":\"Tax Bracket Calculator 2025-2026 | Federal Income Tax Rates\",\"url\":\"https://turbotax.intuit.com/tax-tools/calculators/tax-bracket/\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, I found information about IRS Revenue Procedure 2025-32 and the 2026 tax brackets for head of household filers. However, the search results do not provide the specific dollar amounts you mentioned ($201,750 or $201,775) in connection with head of household tax brackets.\n\nThe search results confirm that Revenue Procedure 2025-32 contains a table providing maximum EITC amount for other categories, income thresholds and phase-outs, and that for heads of households, the standard deduction will be $24,150 for tax year 2026.\n\nHowever, the actual PDF document containing Revenue Procedure 2025-32 appears in the search results (index 4), but the specific tax bracket threshold amounts are not fully displayed in the excerpts provided.\n\nTo find the exact head of household tax bracket threshold of $201,750 or $201,775 referenced in Revenue Procedure 2025-32, you would need to access the full official IRS document directly at https://www.irs.gov/pub/irs-drop/rp-25-32.pdf, which would contain the complete tax rate tables mentioned in the procedure.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9ec58da6-4ff1-4815-8056-168ff90521c1","uuid":"8eb7299b-0bed-496b-8f98-049d558d8221","tool_use_result":{"query":"IRS 2026 \"head of household\" tax brackets \"$201,750\" OR \"$201,775\" revenue procedure 2025-32","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01SrME8HxDA2DiQSLn3mixEa","content":[{"title":"IRS releases tax inflation adjustments for tax year 2026, including amendments from the One, Big, Beautiful Bill | Internal Revenue Service","url":"https://www.irs.gov/newsroom/irs-releases-tax-inflation-adjustments-for-tax-year-2026-including-amendments-from-the-one-big-beautiful