{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01N8eT1VQhM48JVe2njaAzwf","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a much clearer picture. The Doeren source provides complete brackets for HoH, MFS, and MFJ/QSS.\n\nFor Head of Household:\n- 24%: $105,701 - $201,750\n- 32%: $201,751 - $256,200\n\nSo the HoH 24%/32% boundary is $201,750 (not $201,775). This MATCHES the current_value.json.\n\nThe earlier search result that said $201,775 for HoH was incorrect. It probably copied the single filer number.\n\nSo the correct data is:\n\n\nNow I'm looking at the complete Single and MFJ brackets from the source. The Single filer brackets show the 24%/32% boundary at $201,775 with the 32% bracket extending to $256,225, while the MFJ brackets are partially visible but follow the same pattern at double the Single thresholds. Generating tax bracket table... The Doeren source is from a CPA firm that analyzes IRS guidance, so while it's not on the allowed hosts list, it's solid for cross-referencing. Let me systematically verify each filing status against current_value.json to make sure everything lines up correctly. Now I'm verifying the tax bracket thresholds for the remaining filing statuses—Head of Household and Married Filing Separately—to ensure all the income ranges align correctly across the different tax rates.\n\nAll the values check out against the current data. Now I need to pull in the secondary sources to corroborate these numbers, starting with Tax Foundation and then cross-referencing with Kiplinger, but I should first verify what the source policy allows me to use. I've got strong primary confirmation from the IRS newsroom for Single and MFJ brackets, plus a web search synthesis that pulled together all five filing statuses from multiple sources. I also have detailed analysis from a CPA source covering HoH, MFS, and the other statuses. Now I need to clarify which of my sources actually meet the approved secondary host requirements and whether I can get proper confirmations from Tax Foundation or Tax Policy Center.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":430,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3373,"cache_read_input_tokens":47690,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3373,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9ec58da6-4ff1-4815-8056-168ff90521c1","uuid":"be0d1141-976a-4ab3-b9d1-747f0c528f80"}
