{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UM76KnX58ZZdQUXBKSviz6","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"site:taxfoundation.org 2026 tax brackets single married head of household all filing statuses complete table\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"2026 Tax Brackets and Federal Income Tax Rates | Tax Foundation\",\"url\":\"https://taxfoundation.org/data/all/federal/2026-tax-brackets/\"},{\"title\":\"2026 State Income Tax Rates and Brackets | Tax Foundation\",\"url\":\"https://taxfoundation.org/data/all/state/state-income-tax-rates-2026/\"},{\"title\":\"2025 Tax Brackets and Federal Income Tax Rates | Tax Foundation\",\"url\":\"https://taxfoundation.org/data/all/federal/2025-tax-brackets/\"},{\"title\":\"2026 Tax Brackets if the TCJA Expires\",\"url\":\"https://taxfoundation.org/blog/2026-tax-brackets-tax-cuts-and-jobs-act-expires/\"},{\"title\":\"Details and Analysis of Repealing Head of Household Filing Status\",\"url\":\"https://taxfoundation.org/blog/repealing-head-of-household-filing-status/\"},{\"title\":\"2026 State Tax Changes Taking Effect January 1st | Tax Foundation\",\"url\":\"https://taxfoundation.org/research/all/state/2026-state-tax-changes/\"},{\"title\":\"2024 Tax Brackets | 2024-2025 Federal Tax Brackets & Rates\",\"url\":\"https://taxfoundation.org/data/all/federal/2024-tax-brackets/\"},{\"title\":\"2026 Tax Calculator: How the One Big Beautiful Bill Act’s Tax Changes Will Affect You\",\"url\":\"https://taxfoundation.org/data/all/federal/tax-calculator-obbba/\"},{\"title\":\"2025 State Income Tax Rates and Brackets | Tax Foundation\",\"url\":\"https://taxfoundation.org/data/all/state/state-income-tax-rates/\"},{\"title\":\"Tax Brackets | TaxEDU Glossary\",\"url\":\"https://taxfoundation.org/taxedu/glossary/tax-brackets/\"}]\n\nI found the Tax Foundation article on 2026 tax brackets. The search results reference Table 1 as containing the complete 2026 tax bracket information for all filing statuses. Let me access that specific page to get you the complete table data.\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"2026 Tax Brackets and Federal Income Tax Rates | Tax Foundation\",\"url\":\"https://taxfoundation.org/data/all/federal/2026-tax-brackets/\"},{\"title\":\"2026 State Income Tax Rates and Brackets | Tax Foundation\",\"url\":\"https://taxfoundation.org/data/all/state/state-income-tax-rates-2026/\"},{\"title\":\"Federal income tax rates and brackets | Internal Revenue Service\",\"url\":\"https://www.irs.gov/filing/federal-income-tax-rates-and-brackets\"},{\"title\":\"2025-2026 Tax Brackets & Federal Income Tax Rates | H&R Block®\",\"url\":\"https://www.hrblock.com/tax-center/irs/tax-brackets-and-rates/what-are-the-tax-brackets/\"},{\"title\":\"2025 Tax Brackets and Federal Income Tax Rates | Tax Foundation\",\"url\":\"https://taxfoundation.org/data/all/federal/2025-tax-brackets/\"},{\"title\":\"2025-2026 Federal Tax Brackets and Income Rates - NerdWallet\",\"url\":\"https://www.nerdwallet.com/taxes/learn/federal-income-tax-brackets\"},{\"title\":\"2025 and 2026 tax brackets and federal income tax rates | Fidelity\",\"url\":\"https://www.fidelity.com/learning-center/personal-finance/tax-brackets\"},{\"title\":\"2026 individual tax brackets, and tips for understanding what you pay | Principal\",\"url\":\"https://www.principal.com/individuals/learn/individual-tax-brackets-understand-what-you-pay\"},{\"title\":\"2026 Tax Brackets if the TCJA Expires\",\"url\":\"https://taxfoundation.org/blog/2026-tax-brackets-tax-cuts-and-jobs-act-expires/\"},{\"title\":\"Tax Brackets 2026 : Married vs. Single Filing Guide\",\"url\":\"https://swatadvisors.com/irs-tax-brackets-for-2026/\"}]\n\nBased on my web search of the Tax Foundation website, I found that the 2026 tax bracket information is available on their page at taxfoundation.org/data/all/federal/2026-tax-brackets/. \n\nThe income limits for all tax brackets and all filers can be found in Table 1 on that page. However, the search results don't display the complete table data itself—only references to it.\n\nFrom the information available in the search results, I can provide you with these key 2026 tax bracket details:\n\n- The federal income tax has seven tax rates in 2026: 10 percent, 12 percent, 22 percent, 24 percent, 32 percent, 35 percent, and 37 percent.\n\n- The top marginal income tax rate of 37 percent will hit taxpayers with taxable income above $640,600 for single filers and above $768,600 for married couples filing jointly.\n\n- The 32% bracket starts at $201,776 for single filers, compared to $403,551 for married couples filing jointly. The 35% bracket starts at $256,226 for single filers, compared to $512,451 for married couples filing jointly. The 37% bracket begins once taxable income exceeds $640,600 for single filers.\n\nTo view the complete Table 1 with all brackets for all filing statuses (single, married filing jointly, married filing separately, and head of household), you'll need to visit the Tax Foundation page directly at the URL above, as the full table data isn't reproduced in the search results.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9ec58da6-4ff1-4815-8056-168ff90521c1","uuid":"74acca1a-00f8-434f-aa82-e31c8f277229","tool_use_result":{"query":"site:taxfoundation.org 2026 tax brackets single married head of household all filing statuses complete table","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01PcH7yQufikwpGv6BPWTXYb","content":[{"title":"2026 Tax Brackets and Federal Income Tax Rates | Tax Foundation","url":"https://taxfoundation.org/data/all/federal/2026-tax-brackets/"},{"title":"2026 State Income Tax Rates and Brackets | Tax Foundation","url":"https://taxfoundation.org/data/all/state/state-income-tax-rates-2026/"},{"title":"2025 Tax Brackets and Federal Income Tax Rates | Tax Foundation","url":"https://taxfoundation.org/data/all/federal/2025-tax-brackets/"},{"title":"20