{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JViFX6vVE2jRZz8i7HS6Z3","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"kiplinger.com 2026 tax brackets all filing statuses head of household married filing separately\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"2025-2026 Tax Brackets and Marginal Federal Income Tax Rates: What to Know | Kiplinger\",\"url\":\"https://www.kiplinger.com/taxes/tax-brackets/602222/income-tax-brackets\"},{\"title\":\"The Federal Income Tax Brackets for 2026\",\"url\":\"https://www.aarp.org/money/taxes/income-tax-brackets-2026/\"},{\"title\":\"Federal income tax rates and brackets | Internal Revenue Service\",\"url\":\"https://www.irs.gov/filing/federal-income-tax-rates-and-brackets\"},{\"title\":\"IRS Updates 2026 Tax Deduction for People Age 65 and Older | Kiplinger\",\"url\":\"https://www.kiplinger.com/taxes/new-tax-deduction-change-over-65\"},{\"title\":\"New IRS 2026 Tax Brackets Are Set: Will Your Rate Change? | Kiplinger\",\"url\":\"https://www.kiplinger.com/taxes/new-tax-brackets-set\"},{\"title\":\"2026 Tax Brackets and Federal Income Tax Rates | Tax Foundation\",\"url\":\"https://taxfoundation.org/data/all/federal/2026-tax-brackets/\"},{\"title\":\"Tax Season 2026 Is Here: 8 Big Changes to Know Before You File | Kiplinger\",\"url\":\"https://www.kiplinger.com/taxes/big-tax-changes-to-know-before-you-file\"},{\"title\":\"2025-2026 Tax Brackets & Federal Income Tax Rates | H&R Block®\",\"url\":\"https://www.hrblock.com/tax-center/irs/tax-brackets-and-rates/what-are-the-tax-brackets/\"},{\"title\":\"2026 IRS Tax Brackets, Standard Deductions, Capital Gains +AMT\",\"url\":\"https://millancpa.com/insights/2026-irs-tax-brackets-standard-deductions-capital-gains-amt\"},{\"title\":\"What's the Standard Deduction for 2025 and 2026? How It Works Plus Updated Amounts | Kiplinger\",\"url\":\"https://www.kiplinger.com/taxes/tax-deductions/602223/standard-deduction\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, I found information from Kiplinger and other sources about the 2026 tax brackets. Here's what I found:\n\n## 2026 Tax Brackets and Standard Deductions\n\nThe IRS has revealed 2026 tax brackets that you'll use for tax returns typically filed in early 2027. The associated tax rates remain the same at 10%, 12%, 22%, 24%, 32%, 35%, and 37%.\n\n### Standard Deduction Amounts for 2026:\n\nThe standard deduction for 2026 will be $16,100 for single filers and married individuals filing separately, while the amount for those married filing jointly will be $32,200.\n\nFor Head of Household, the 2026 standard deduction is $23,950.\n\nThe search results from Kiplinger's main tax brackets page contain references to 2026 bracket information, but the specific income ranges for each filing status (head of household and married filing separately) are not fully displayed in these search result excerpts. To see the complete detailed tax bracket tables with all income ranges for each filing status on Kiplinger.com, you would need to visit their full article directly at: https://www.kiplinger.com/taxes/tax-brackets/602222/income-tax-brackets\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9ec58da6-4ff1-4815-8056-168ff90521c1","uuid":"90cc57e1-ab03-4179-b08e-5704bb10b7ba","tool_use_result":{"query":"kiplinger.com 2026 tax brackets all filing statuses head of household married filing separately","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01VdzP2MgTZrCci51QpJb9b6","content":[{"title":"2025-2026 Tax Brackets and Marginal Federal Income Tax Rates: What to Know | Kiplinger","url":"https://www.kiplinger.com/taxes/tax-brackets/602222/income-tax-brackets"},{"title":"The Federal Income Tax Brackets for 2026","url":"https://www.aarp.org/money/taxes/income-tax-brackets-2026/"},{"title":"Federal income tax rates and brackets | Internal Revenue Service","url":"https://www.irs.gov/filing/federal-income-tax-rates-and-brackets"},{"title":"IRS Updates 2026 Tax Deduction for People Age 65 and Older | Kiplinger","url":"https://www.kiplinger.com/taxes/new-tax-deduction-change-over-65"},{"title":"New IRS 2026 Tax Brackets Are Set: Will Your Rate Change? | Kiplinger","url":"https://www.kiplinger.com/taxes/new-tax-brackets-set"},{"title":"2026 Tax Brackets and Federal Income Tax Rates | Tax Foundation","url":"https://taxfoundation.org/data/all/federal/2026-tax-brackets/"},{"title":"Tax Season 2026 Is Here: 8 Big Changes to Know Before You File | Kiplinger","url":"https://www.kiplinger.com/taxes/big-tax-changes-to-know-before-you-file"},{"title":"2025-2026 Tax Brackets & Federal Income Tax Rates | H&R Block®","url":"https://www.hrblock.com/tax-center/irs/tax-brackets-and-rates/what-are-the-tax-brackets/"},{"title":"2026 IRS Tax Brackets, Standard Deductions, Capital Gains +AMT","url":"https://millancpa.com/insights/2026-irs-tax-brackets-standard-deductions-capital-gains-amt"},{"title":"What's the Standard Deduction for 2025 and 2026? How It Works Plus Updated Amounts | Kiplinger","url":"https://www.kiplinger.com/taxes/tax-deductions/602223/standard-deduction"}]},"Based on the search results, I found information from Kiplinger and other sources about the 2026 tax brackets. Here's what I found:\n\n## 2026 Tax Brackets and Standard Deductions\n\nThe IRS has revealed 2026 tax brackets that you'll use for tax returns typically filed in early 2027. The associated tax rates remain the same at 10%, 12%, 22%, 24%, 32%, 35%, and 37%.\n\n### Standard Deduction Amounts for 2026:\n\nThe standard deduction for 2026 will be $16,100 for single filers and married individuals filing separately, while the amount for those married filing jointly will be $32,200.\n\nFor Head of Household, the 2026 standard deduction is $23,950.\n\nThe search results from Kiplinger's main tax brackets page contain references to 2026 bracket information, but the specific income ranges for each filing status (head of household and married