{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Qfhn1d2XvyoH9dRTAVBsCs","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Both files have been written. Here's a summary of the verification:\n\n**Result**: All 2026 federal income tax brackets for all five filing statuses match the current embedded values exactly. No changes needed.\n\n**Sources used**:\n- **Primary**: IRS Rev Proc 2025-32 and IRS Newsroom release IR-2025-103 (irs.gov)\n- **Secondary**: Tax Foundation (approved host), Doeren Mayhew CPAs (not on approved list)\n\n**Key details**:\n- Seven rates (10%–37%) confirmed, made permanent by OBBBA § 70101\n- Single and MFJ brackets directly confirmed from IRS newsroom\n- HoH and MFS brackets confirmed via Doeren Mayhew's analysis of Rev Proc 2025-32\n- QSS brackets identical to MFJ per IRC § 1(a)\n\n**Flagged issues**:\n1. Only 1 of 2 required secondary confirmations from approved hosts (Tax Foundation). Kiplinger returned 403; Tax Policy Center had no bracket page. A reviewer should manually verify.\n2. The Rev Proc PDF couldn't be parsed directly — HoH/MFS rely on secondary source corroboration.\n3. Minor HoH 24%/32% boundary discrepancy across web sources ($201,750 vs $201,775) was resolved in favor of $201,750, consistent with historical IRS rounding patterns and the more detailed Doeren source."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2930,"cache_read_input_tokens":67389,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2930,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9ec58da6-4ff1-4815-8056-168ff90521c1","uuid":"ee4a9cf1-5ec9-4cda-b1de-1b0c95025418"}
